It has already been noticed¹ that Soutra and Fala were united to his parish in 1574, but they were again disjoined in 1589, Johnstoun continuing minister of Creichtoun‚ as well as provost, and en- joying the thirds of his benefice, with “ the manse gleib and kirkland of Creichtoun.’' In the year 1595, his stipend was “the haill Provostrie of Creichtoun quherunto he wes provydit, 1:133, 6s. 8d.” From incidental notices in Calderwood‚ he appears to have taken an active share in church matters, and to have been a zealous friend of Presbyterian church govern- ment.
